fields.title: Find Minimum in Rotated Sorted Array
fields.description: Suppose an array sorted in ascending order is rotated at some pivot unknown to you beforehand. Find the minimum element.

fields.title: Search in Rotated Sorted Array
fields.description: Suppose an array sorted in ascending order is rotated at some pivot unknown to you beforehand. You are given a target value to search. If found in the array, return its index, otherwise return -1.

fields.title: Time Based Key-Value Store
fields.description: Design a time-based key-value data structure that can store multiple values for the same key at different time stamps and retrieve the key's value at a certain timestamp.

fields.title: Median of Two Sorted Arrays
fields.description: Given two sorted arrays nums1 and nums2 of size m and n respectively, return the median of the two sorted arrays.

fields.title: Kth Largest Element in an Array
fields.description: Find the kth largest element in an unsorted array.

fields.title: Last Stone Weight
fields.description: We have a collection of stones, each stone has a positive integer weight. Each turn, we choose the two heaviest stones and smash them together.

fields.title: Task Scheduler
fields.description: Given a characters array tasks, representing the tasks a CPU needs to do, where each letter represents a different task. Tasks could be done in any order.

fields.title: Design Twitter
fields.description: Design a simplified version of Twitter where users can post tweets, follow/unfollow another user, and is able to see the 10 most recent tweets in the user's news feed.

fields.title: Find Median from Data Stream
fields.description: Design a data structure that supports the following two operations: addNum(int num) - Add a integer number from the data stream to the data structure. findMedian() - Return the median of all elements so far.

fields.title: Sliding Window Maximum
fields.description: You are given an array of integers nums, there is a sliding window of size k which is moving from the very left of the array to the very right.

fields.title: Climbing Stairs
fields.description: You are climbing a staircase. It takes n steps to reach the top. Each time you can either climb 1 or 2 steps.

fields.title: Coin Change
fields.description: You are given an integer array coins representing coins of different denominations and an integer amount representing a total amount of money.

fields.title: Longest Increasing Subsequence
fields.description: Given an integer array nums, return the length of the longest strictly increasing subsequence.

fields.title: Longest Common Subsequence
fields.description: Given two strings text1 and text2, return the length of their longest common subsequence.

fields.title: Word Break
fields.description: Given a string s and a dictionary of strings wordDict, return true if s can be segmented into a space-separated sequence of one or more dictionary words.

fields.title: Combination Sum
fields.description: Given an array of distinct integers candidates and a target integer target, return a list of all unique combinations of candidates where the chosen numbers sum to target.

fields.title: House Robber
fields.description: You are a professional robber planning to rob houses along a street. Each house has a certain amount of money stashed, the only constraint stopping you from robbing each of them is that adjacent houses have security systems connected.

fields.title: House Robber II
fields.description: You are a professional robber planning to rob houses along a street. Each house has a certain amount of money stashed, the only constraint stopping you from robbing each of them is that adjacent houses have security systems connected. All houses at this place are arranged in a circle.

fields.title: Decode Ways
fields.description: A message containing letters from A-Z can be encoded into numbers using the following mapping: 'A' -> '1', 'B' -> '2', ... 'Z' -> '26'. To decode an encoded message, all the digits must be grouped then mapped back to letters.

fields.title: Unique Paths
fields.description: A robot is located at the top-left corner of a m x n grid. The robot can only move either down or right at any point in time. The robot is trying to reach the bottom-right corner of the grid.

fields.title: Jump Game
fields.description: Given an array of non-negative integers nums, you are initially positioned at the first index of the array. Each element in the array represents your maximum jump length at that position. Determine if you are able to reach the last index.

fields.title: Merge Intervals
fields.description: Given an array of intervals where intervals[i] = [starti, endi], merge all overlapping intervals, and return an array of the non-overlapping intervals that cover all the intervals in the input.

fields.title: Insert Interval
fields.description: You are given an array of non-overlapping intervals intervals where intervals[i] = [starti, endi] representing the start and the end of the ith interval and intervals are sorted in ascending order by starti. You are also given an interval newInterval = [start, end] that represents the start and end of another interval. Insert newInterval into intervals such that intervals is still sorted in ascending order by starti and intervals still do not have any overlapping intervals (merge overlapping intervals if necessary).

fields.title: Non-overlapping Intervals
fields.description: Given an array of intervals intervals where intervals[i] = [starti, endi], return the minimum number of intervals you need to remove to make the rest of the intervals non-overlapping.

fields.title: Meeting Rooms
fields.description: Given an array of meeting time intervals where intervals[i] = [starti, endi], determine if a person could attend all meetings.

fields.title: Meeting Rooms II
fields.description: Given an array of meeting time intervals intervals where intervals[i] = [starti, endi], return the minimum number of conference rooms required.

fields.title: Rotate Image
fields.description: You are given an n x n 2D matrix representing an image, rotate the image by 90 degrees (clockwise).

fields.title: Spiral Matrix
fields.description: Given an m x n matrix, return all elements of the matrix in spiral order.

fields.title: Set Matrix Zeroes
fields.description: Given an m x n integer matrix matrix, if an element is 0, set its entire row and column to 0's, and return the matrix.

fields.title: Word Search
fields.description: Given an m x n grid of characters board and a string word, return true if word exists in the grid.

fields.title: Number of Islands
fields.description: Given an m x n 2D binary grid grid which represents a map of '1's (land) and '0's (water), return the number of islands.

fields.title: Clone Graph
fields.description: Given a reference of a node in a connected undirected graph, return a deep copy (clone) of the graph.

fields.title: Max Area of Island
fields.description: You are given an m x n binary matrix grid. An island is a group of 1's (representing land) connected 4-directionally (horizontal or vertical).

fields.title: Pacific Atlantic Water Flow
fields.description: There is an m x n rectangular island that borders both the Pacific Ocean and Atlantic Ocean. The Pacific Ocean touches the island's left and top edges, and the Atlantic Ocean touches the island's right and bottom edges.

fields.title: Surrounded Regions
fields.description: Given an m x n matrix board containing 'X' and 'O', capture all regions surrounded by 'X'.

fields.title: Course Schedule
fields.description: There are a total of numCourses courses you have to take, labeled from 0 to numCourses - 1. You are given an array prerequisites where prerequisites[i] = [ai, bi] indicates that you must take course bi first if you want to take course ai.

fields.title: Course Schedule II
fields.description: There are a total of numCourses courses you have to take, labeled from 0 to numCourses - 1. You are given an array prerequisites where prerequisites[i] = [ai, bi] indicates that you must take course bi first if you want to take course ai.

fields.title: Graph Valid Tree
fields.description: You have a graph of n nodes labeled from 0 to n - 1. You are given an integer n and a list of edges where edges[i] = [ai, bi] indicates that there is an undirected edge between nodes ai and bi in the graph.

fields.title: Number of Connected Components in an Undirected Graph
fields.description: You have a graph of n nodes. You are given an integer n and an array edges where edges[i] = [ai, bi] indicates that there is an edge between ai and bi in the graph.

fields.title: Reconstruct Itinerary
fields.description: You are given a list of airline tickets where tickets[i] = [fromi, toi] represent the departure and arrival airports of one flight. Reconstruct the itinerary in order and return it.

fields.title: Valid Parentheses
fields.description: Given a string s containing just the characters '(', ')', '{', '}', '[' and ']', determine if the input string is valid.

fields.title: Generate Parentheses
fields.description: Given n pairs of parentheses, write a function to generate all combinations of well-formed parentheses.

fields.title: Daily Temperatures
fields.description: Given an array of integers temperatures represents the daily temperatures, return an array answer such that answer[i] is the number of days you have to wait after the ith day to get a warmer temperature.

fields.title: Car Fleet
fields.description: There are n cars going to the same destination along a one-lane road. The destination is target miles away.

fields.title: Largest Rectangle in Histogram
fields.description: Given an array of integers heights representing the histogram's bar height where the width of each bar is 1, return the area of the largest rectangle in the histogram.

fields.title: Binary Tree Inorder Traversal
fields.description: Given the root of a binary tree, return the inorder traversal of its nodes' values.

fields.title: Binary Tree Level Order Traversal
fields.description: Given the root of a binary tree, return the level order traversal of its nodes' values.

fields.title: Binary Tree Right Side View
fields.description: Given the root of a binary tree, imagine yourself standing on the right side of it, return the values of the nodes you can see ordered from top to bottom.

fields.title: Count Good Nodes in Binary Tree
fields.description: Given a binary tree root, a node X in the tree is named good if in the path from root to X there are no nodes with a value greater than X.

fields.title: Validate Binary Search Tree
fields.description: Given the root of a binary tree, determine if it is a valid binary search tree (BST).

fields.title: Kth Smallest Element in a BST
fields.description: Given the root of a binary search tree, and an integer k, return the kth smallest value (1-indexed) of all the values of the nodes in the tree.

fields.title: Lowest Common Ancestor of a BST
fields.description: Given a binary search tree (BST), find the lowest common ancestor (LCA) of two given nodes in the BST.

fields.title: Implement Trie (Prefix Tree)
fields.description: A trie (pronounced as 'try') or prefix tree is a tree data structure used to efficiently store and retrieve keys in a dataset of strings.

fields.title: Add and Search Word
fields.description: Design a data structure that supports adding new words and finding if a string matches any previously added string.

fields.title: Word Search II
fields.description: Given an m x n board of characters and a list of strings words, return all words on the board.

fields.title: Merge K Sorted Lists
fields.description: You are given an array of k linked-lists lists, each linked-list is sorted in ascending order.

fields.title: Reverse Nodes in k-Group
fields.description: Given a linked list, reverse the nodes of a linked list k at a time and return its modified list.

fields.title: Reverse Linked List
fields.description: Given the head of a singly linked list, reverse the list, and return the reversed list.

fields.title: Detect Cycle in a Linked List
fields.description: Given a linked list, return the node where the cycle begins. If there is no cycle, return null.

fields.title: Copy List with Random Pointer
fields.description: A linked list of length n is given such that each node contains an additional random pointer which could point to any node in the list, or null.

fields.title: LRU Cache
fields.description: Design and implement a data structure for Least Recently Used (LRU) cache. It should support the following operations: get and put.

fields.title: Min Stack
fields.description: Design a stack that supports push, pop, top, and retrieving the minimum element in constant time.

fields.title: LFU Cache
fields.description: Design and implement a data structure for Least Frequently Used (LFU) cache.

fields.title: Design Circular Deque
fields.description: Design your implementation of the circular double-ended queue (deque).

fields.title: Design HashMap
fields.description: Design a HashMap without using any built-in hash table libraries.

fields.title: Design HashSet
fields.description: Design a HashSet without using any built-in hash table libraries.

fields.title: Add Two Numbers
fields.description: You are given two non-empty linked lists representing two non-negative integers. The digits are stored in reverse order, and each of their nodes contains a single digit.

fields.title: Merge Two Sorted Lists
fields.description: Merge two sorted linked lists and return it as a sorted list. The list should be made by splicing together the nodes of the first two lists.

fields.title: Remove Nth Node From End of List
fields.description: Given the head of a linked list, remove the nth node from the end of the list and return its head.

fields.title: Swap Nodes in Pairs
fields.description: Given a linked list, swap every two adjacent nodes and return its head.

fields.title: Reverse Linked List II
fields.description: Reverse a linked list from position m to n. Do it in one-pass.

fields.title: Intersection of Two Linked Lists
fields.description: Write a program to find the node at which the intersection of two singly linked lists begins.

fields.title: Linked List Cycle
fields.description: Given head, the head of a linked list, determine if the linked list has a cycle in it.

fields.title: Linked List Cycle II
fields.description: Given a linked list, return the node where the cycle begins. If there is no cycle, return null.

fields.title: Reverse Linked List III
fields.description: Reverse a linked list from position m to n. Do it in one-pass.

fields.title: Design Circular Queue
fields.description: Design your implementation of the circular queue. The circular queue is a linear data structure in which the operations are performed based on FIFO (First In First Out) principle and the last position is connected back to the first position to make a circle.

fields.title: Design Browser History
fields.description: You have a browser of one tab where you start on the homepage and you can visit another url, get back in the history, and forward in the history.

fields.title: Insert Delete GetRandom O(1)
fields.description: Design a data structure that supports all following operations in average O(1) time.

fields.title: Maximum Product Subarray
fields.description: Given an integer array nums, find a contiguous non-empty subarray within the array that has the largest product, and return the product.

fields.title: Find Minimum in Rotated Sorted Array
fields.description: Suppose an array of length n sorted in ascending order is rotated between 1 and n times. Return the minimum element of this array.

fields.title: Search in Rotated Sorted Array II
fields.description: Suppose an array sorted in ascending order is rotated at some pivot unknown to you beforehand. You are given a target value to search. If found in the array return true, otherwise return false.

fields.title: Unique Paths
fields.description: A robot is located at the top-left corner of a m x n grid. The robot can only move either down or right at any point in time. The robot is trying to reach the bottom-right corner of the grid.

fields.title: House Robber
fields.description: You are a professional robber planning to rob houses along a street. Each house has a certain amount of money stashed, the only constraint stopping you from robbing each of them is that adjacent houses have security systems connected and it will automatically contact the police if two adjacent houses were broken into on the same night.

fields.title: Coin Change
fields.description: You are given coins of different denominations and a total amount of money amount. Write a function to compute the fewest number of coins that you need to make up that amount. If that amount of money cannot be made up by any combination of the coins, return -1.

fields.title: Longest Increasing Subsequence
fields.description: Given an integer array nums, return the length of the longest strictly increasing subsequence.

fields.title: Maximum Subarray
fields.description: Given an integer array nums, find the contiguous subarray (containing at least one number) which has the largest sum and return its sum.

fields.title: Best Time to Buy and Sell Stock
fields.description: You are given an array prices where prices[i] is the price of a given stock on the ith day. You want to maximize your profit by choosing a single day to buy one stock and choosing a different day in the future to sell that stock.

fields.title: Best Time to Buy and Sell Stock II
fields.description: You are given an array prices where prices[i] is the price of a given stock on the ith day. Find the maximum profit you can achieve. You may complete as many transactions as you like (i.e., buy one and sell one share of the stock multiple times).

fields.title: Best Time to Buy and Sell Stock III
fields.description: You are given an array prices where prices[i] is the price of a given stock on the ith day. Find the maximum profit you can achieve. You may complete at most two transactions.

fields.title: Best Time to Buy and Sell Stock IV
fields.description: You are given an integer array prices where prices[i] is the price of a given stock on the ith day, and an integer k. Find the maximum profit you can achieve. You may complete at most k transactions.

fields.title: Regular Expression Matching
fields.description:
Given an input string s and a pattern p, implement regular expression matching with support for '.' and '*' where: 
'.' Matches any single character. 
'*' Matches zero or more of the preceding element.

fields.title: Wildcard Matching
fields.description:
Given an input string (s) and a pattern (p), implement wildcard pattern matching with support for '?' and '*' where: 
'?' Matches any single character. 
'*' Matches any sequence of characters (including the empty sequence).

fields.title: Longest Palindromic Substring
fields.description: Given a string s, return the longest palindromic substring in s.

fields.title: Integer to Roman
fields.description: Given an integer, convert it to a roman numeral.

fields.title: Roman to Integer
fields.description: Given a roman numeral, convert it to an integer.

fields.title: Valid Palindrome
fields.description: Given a string s, determine if it is a palindrome, considering only alphanumeric characters and ignoring cases.

fields.title: Longest Common Prefix
fields.description: Write a function to find the longest common prefix string amongst an array of strings. If there is no common prefix, return an empty string ''.

fields.title: Substring with Concatenation of All Words
fields.description: You are given a string s and an array of strings words of the same length. Return all starting indices of substring(s) in s that is a concatenation of each word in words exactly once, in any order, and without any intervening characters.

fields.title: Implement strStr()
fields.description: Return the index of the first occurrence of needle in haystack, or -1 if needle is not part of haystack.

fields.title: Multiply Strings
fields.description: Given two non-negative integers num1 and num2 represented as strings, return the product of num1 and num2, also represented as a string.

fields.title: ZigZag Conversion
fields.description:
The string "PAYPALISHIRING" is written in a zigzag pattern on a given number of rows like this: (you may want to display this pattern in a fixed font for better legibility) 
P   A   H   N 
A P L S I I G 
Y   I   R 
And then read line by line: "PAHNAPLSIIGYIR". Write the code that will take a string and make this conversion given a number of rows.

fields.description: Given a string s containing just the characters '(', ')', '{', '}', '[' and ']', determine if the input string is valid.

fields.title: Generate Parentheses
fields.description: Given n pairs of parentheses, write a function to generate all combinations of well-formed parentheses.

fields.title: Longest Valid Parentheses
fields.description: Given a string containing just the characters '(' and ')', find the length of the longest valid (well-formed) parentheses substring.

fields.title: Count and Say
fields.description:
The count-and-say sequence is a sequence of digit strings defined by the recursive formula: 
- countAndSay(1) = "1" 
- countAndSay(n) is the way you would "say" the digit string from countAndSay(n-1), which is then converted into a different digit string.

fields.title: Decode Ways
fields.description:
A message containing letters from A-Z can be encoded into numbers using the following mapping: 
'A' -> "1" 
'B' -> "2" 
... 
'Z' -> "26" 
To decode an encoded message, all the digits must be grouped then mapped back into letters using the reverse of the mapping above (there may be multiple ways).

fields.title: Letter Combinations of a Phone Number
fields.description: Given a string containing digits from 2-9 inclusive, return all possible letter combinations that the number could represent. Return the answer in any order.

fields.description: Given an array nums of n integers and an integer target, find three integers in nums such that the sum is closest to target. Return the sum of the three integers. You may assume that each input would have exactly one solution.

a, b, c, and d are distinct. 
nums[a] + nums[b] + nums[c] + nums[d] == target
